Fast Fashion vs. Fashion Industry: A Data-Driven Customer Review Analysis

📌 Overview

This project analyzes customer reviews of Fast Fashion brands and compares them with the overall Fashion Industry using Public Yelp Data. The goal is to uncover insights into customer sentiment, store performance, and brand positioning through data-driven analysis.

📊 Key Findings

Fast Fashion brands have a lower average rating (2.79⭐) compared to other fashion brands (3.64⭐), indicating potential concerns with product quality and service.
Customer sentiment analysis using NLP (BERT) reveals that affordability and trendiness are key strengths of Fast Fashion, while complaints focus on product quality and customer service.
Store distribution and market trends suggest key expansion opportunities in Pennsylvania (PA), New Jersey (NJ), and Arizona (AZ).
Sustainability is a growing concern, with traditional brands leading the conversation, while Fast Fashion brands lag in this area.
🛠️ Tech Stack & Methods

Data Source: Public Yelp Data
Programming: Python (Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn)
Natural Language Processing (NLP): BERT for sentiment analysis
Visualization: Data-driven insights into market trends
📂 Project Files

analysis.ipynb - Jupyter Notebook with full data analysis
presentation.pdf - Research summary and key insights
README.md - Project documentation
🚀 How to Run

Clone this repository:
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/fast-fashion-analysis.git
Open analysis.ipynb in Jupyter Notebook or Google Colab.
Install dependencies if needed:
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn transformers
Run the notebook to explore insights.
📢 Insights & Business Applications

Fast Fashion brands should improve product quality and customer service while expanding into strategic markets.
Luxury and traditional fashion brands should emphasize sustainability and craftsmanship to enhance brand loyalty.
The study provides valuable insights for retail strategists, brand managers, and marketing analysts.
